        body: "Exchange rates are determined by several theoretical frameworks. Purchasing Power Parity (PPP) — the exchange rate adjusts so that a basket of goods costs the same in both countries. Absolute PPP: S = Pa / Pb. Relative PPP: % change in S = Inflation differential (πa − πb). Interest Rate Parity (IRP) — the forward premium/discount equals the interest rate differential between two countries to prevent arbitrage. Fisher Effect: Nominal rate = Real rate + Inflation rate. Balance of Payments theory — exchange rate adjusts to maintain BoP equilibrium; sustained CAD leads to currency depreciation.",
        highlight: "Relative PPP: e% ≈ πIndia − πUS | IRP: Forward Premium = (r India − r US) / (1 + r US) | CAD → Rupee weakens"
