        body: "Job Analysis is the systematic process of collecting information about the duties, responsibilities, required skills, outcomes, and work environment of a job. It is the foundation for all HRM functions. Two key outputs: Job Description (JD) — a written statement describing job tasks, duties, responsibilities, working conditions, and relationships; and Job Specification (JS) / Person Specification — describes the minimum qualifications, skills, experience, and personal traits required to perform the job. Job Evaluation assesses the relative worth of jobs within an organisation to establish a rational, equitable pay structure.",
