        body: "When a borrower's credit requirements exceed a single bank's prudential exposure limit or capacity, multiple banks finance the borrower. Two arrangements exist: Consortium Lending — a formal arrangement where multiple banks jointly finance a single borrower under a common credit appraisal, common loan documentation, and common security with a Lead Bank coordinating. All banks share in proportion to their agreed share. Multiple Banking (MB) — each bank independently finances the borrower without coordination. Banks operate in silos with separate documentation and security. RBI has gradually moved away from mandatory consortium, but consortium is still preferred for large borrowers (credit limits above ₹500 Cr, though not mandatory after 1997 deregulation).",
