          { e: "📍", n: "Corner Point Theorem", d: "Optimal solution always occurs at a corner (vertex) of the feasible region. Evaluate the objective function at ALL corner points and select the maximum (for maximisation) or minimum (for minimisation). Interior points are never optimal in LP." },
          { e: "🏦", n: "Banking LP Applications", d: "Banks use LP for: asset-liability portfolio optimisation (maximise return subject to capital/liquidity constraints), branch staff scheduling (minimise costs subject to coverage), credit limit allocation across segments. Linear programming is foundational to bank ALCO decisions." }
