          { e: "🌩️", n: "Scenario Analysis", d: "Combines multiple risk factor shocks simultaneously — e.g., 2008 crisis scenario: equity −40%, credit spreads +300 bps, volatility ×3. More realistic but harder to interpret if many scenarios used." },
          { e: "🔄", n: "Stress VaR (SVaR)", d: "Basel III requires Stressed VaR — VaR computed using a 12-month stress period (e.g., 2008 crisis data) applied to current portfolio. SVaR ≥ VaR typically. Market risk capital = max(VaR, 3×avg VaR) + max(SVaR, 3×avg SVaR)." }
