          { e: "🔄", n: "Countercyclical Capital Buffer (CCyB)", d: "0–2.5% of RWA, activated by national regulators when credit growth is excessive (credit bubble risk). RBI can activate CCyB for Indian banks. Currently 0% in India. Designed to cool credit cycles." },
          { e: "🏦", n: "D-SIB / G-SIB Buffer", d: "Domestic Systemically Important Banks (D-SIBs): SBI (0.6%), HDFC Bank (0.2%), ICICI Bank (0.2%) in India. Additional CET1 buffer of 0.2–0.6% on top of CCB. Too-big-to-fail banks must hold more capital." }
