        body: "The RBI Large Exposure Framework (effective April 2019) limits concentration risk — the risk of excessive exposure to a single counterparty or group. Based on Basel Committee's Large Exposures Standard. Key limits: Single Counterparty: Exposure ≤ 25% of Eligible Capital Base (Tier 1 capital). For inter-bank exposures between D-SIBs: ≤ 15% of Eligible Capital Base. Group of Connected Counterparties: Exposure ≤ 25% of Eligible Capital Base (aggregate for all entities in a connected group). Exposure = sum of all credit exposures — loans, bonds, guarantees, derivatives (replacement cost + add-on). Breaches must be reported to RBI and remediated within a specified timeline.",
        highlight: "LEF: Single counterparty ≤ 25% Tier 1 | D-SIB to D-SIB: ≤ 15% | Connected group: ≤ 25% | Effective April 2019"
