          { e: "📉", n: "Floating Rate Payer", d: "Pays floating rate; receives fixed rate. Benefits when rates FALL. Used by fixed-rate borrowers wanting to benefit from falling rates. Banks pay floating/receive fixed on IRS to match floating-rate asset portfolios." },
          { e: "🏦", n: "Bank ALM Use of IRS", d: "If bank has long-fixed assets (loans) funded by short-term deposits, it faces rate risk when rates rise. Bank pays fixed / receives floating on IRS — converts fixed income to floating → reduces duration gap. ALCO may mandate IRS hedging." }
