        steps: [
          "Deposit margin: FTP received (7.2%) − Deposit rate paid (6.5%) = +0.7% → Branch A earns 70 bps for mobilising deposit.",
          "Loan margin: Loan rate (10.5%) − FTP paid to treasury (7.8%) = +2.7% → Branch A earns 270 bps on the loan (credit spread + operating profit).",
          "Treasury: Buys 3-yr funds from branch at 7.8%, sold 1-yr funds to branch at 7.2%. Treasury earns 60 bps on maturity transformation (borrow short at 7.2%, lend long at 7.8%).",
          "If rates rise, treasury bears the risk — it funded long (3yr) by rolling short (1yr) deposits. Branch is insulated.",
          "Total bank spread = Loan rate − Deposit rate = 10.5% − 6.5% = 4.0%. Allocated: Branch = 0.7% + 2.7% = 3.4%; Treasury = 0.6%."
        ],
