          "Aggregation rule: Banks must aggregate cash transactions per customer per month — combined = ₹19,30,000 > ₹10 Lakh threshold. CTR is required for the month.",
          "Structuring is itself an independent offence under PMLA (Section 3) — intent to evade reporting requirements.",
          "Bank obligation: (a) File CTR for the month (aggregated above ₹10 Lakh). (b) File STR within 7 days of identifying the structured pattern as suspicious — regardless of CTR obligation.",
