          { e: "🔍", n: "Compounding", d: "FEMA contraventions can be 'compounded' (settled) by paying a negotiated penalty. Compounding authority: RBI (for violations involving forex ≤ ₹10 Crore) or ED (> ₹10 Crore). Simplifies enforcement — common for technical/inadvertent violations." },
          { e: "🏛️", n: "ED vs. RBI", d: "RBI enforces FEMA for banks and most entities administratively. ED (Enforcement Directorate) handles serious/willful FEMA violations and investigates potential links to PMLA (money laundering). ED can attach proceeds of FEMA violations under PMLA." }
