          { e: "💰", n: "Part Payment (Sec 19)", d: "Part payment of interest or principal by or on behalf of the debtor (before limitation expiry) revives a fresh 3-year limitation from date of payment. Banks must ensure part payments are received and documented before limitation runs out." },
          { e: "⚠️", n: "Time-barred Debts & NPA", d: "Time-barred debts are still debts — they cannot be recovered through court but the debtor's moral obligation survives. Banks cannot sue in court. SARFAESI enforcement also becomes time-barred. Banks must track limitation dates carefully in NPA accounts." }
