        body: "The Credit Information Companies (Regulation) Act, 2005 (CICRA) provides the legal framework for credit information companies (CICs / credit bureaus) in India. RBI regulates CICs under CICRA. Currently four licensed CICs: CIBIL (TransUnion), Equifax, Experian, and CRIF High Mark. Banks and financial institutions are compulsorily required to become 'Credit Institutions' (members) and must submit credit data on all borrowers to all four bureaus. The CIBIL score ranges from 300–900; 750+ is generally considered good. Data includes repayment history, outstanding balances, enquiries, and defaults.",
