        title: "Using CIBIL in Loan Sanction",
        problem: "A customer applies for a ₹50 lakh home loan. The bank pulls his CIBIL report and finds: score 680, one 60-day overdue 18 months ago (now cleared), two active loans with good track record, and 6 loan enquiries in the last 3 months. How should the bank interpret this?",
