        body: "Microfinance involves small-ticket loans to low-income households (LIH) for income generation, household needs, and emergencies. RBI's Regulatory Framework for Microfinance Loans (Master Direction, March 2022) applies to all regulated entities — banks, NBFCs, MFIs, SFBs — creating a unified framework. Key feature: household income ceiling (rural: ₹1.25 lakh p.a.; urban/semi-urban: ₹2 lakh p.a.) and household indebtedness ceiling (total microfinance loans of household ≤ ₹3 lakh). NBFC-MFIs (Microfinance Institutions) are a dedicated category regulated by RBI with a minimum 85% qualifying microfinance asset portfolio requirement.",
