          { e: "✍️", n: "Digital Signature", d: "Section 5: digital signatures have legal validity equal to handwritten signatures. Banks use DSC (Digital Signature Certificates) for secure transactions, e-filing, and government portal access." },
          { e: "📧", n: "Electronic Contracts", d: "Section 10A: contracts formed electronically are valid. Online banking terms & conditions accepted by customer are legally enforceable contracts." },
          { e: "🆔", n: "Sec 66C — Identity Theft", d: "Punishment: up to 3 years imprisonment + ₹1 lakh fine. Using another person's password/electronic signature — covers ATM card skimming, account takeover, SIM swap frauds." },
          { e: "🎣", n: "Sec 66D — Phishing", d: "Punishment: up to 3 years + ₹1 lakh fine. Cheating by personation using computer/internet — covers phishing emails, fake bank websites, vishing calls impersonating bank officials." },
          { e: "🛡️", n: "Sec 43A — Data Protection", d: "Body corporate (including banks) that negligently fails to implement 'reasonable security practices' for sensitive personal data and causes wrongful loss → liable to pay compensation. No cap on compensation." },
          { e: "🚨", n: "CERT-In", d: "Computer Emergency Response Team India — national cyber security agency. Banks must report cyber security incidents (including fraud) to CERT-In within specified timelines (critical incidents: 6 hours under 2022 directions)." }
