        title: "RTI Act 2005: Transparency Obligations for Banks",
        body: "The Right to Information Act, 2005 provides citizens the right to access information held by 'public authorities'. For banking: Public Sector Banks (SBI, nationalised banks, RRBs) are covered as 'public authorities' — citizens can file RTI applications for information about their accounts, loan processing procedures, service charges, RBI circulars, and bank policies. Private banks are NOT directly covered by RTI as they are not public authorities — though RBI (being a public authority) can be asked about regulations applicable to private banks. Under Section 8, certain information is exempt: bank customer data (third-party information), commercially sensitive information, and information prejudicial to national security.",
