        body: "Corporate restructuring involves reorganising a company's structure, operations, or finances to improve efficiency or unlock value. Expansion: mergers, acquisitions, JVs. Contraction: sell-offs (divestiture), spin-offs, demergers, carve-outs. A Demerger (India: Section 2(19AA) of Income Tax Act, Sections 230-232 Companies Act) transfers one or more undertakings to a new/existing company, with consideration paid in shares. Spin-off: existing shareholders receive shares of subsidiary directly. Share Buyback: company repurchases own shares — EPS accretive, signals undervaluation. Restructuring is used to eliminate 'conglomerate discount' (sum-of-parts > whole company value).",
