        body: "Public-Private Partnerships (PPPs) are arrangements where government and private sector jointly deliver infrastructure — combining government's land/concession with private sector's capital, construction efficiency, and operational expertise. India's National Highway programme uses multiple PPP models. The choice of PPP model determines: who bears traffic risk, how construction is financed, and how the private partner earns returns. Key models: BOT-Toll (private bears traffic risk), DBFOT (Design-Build-Finance-Operate-Transfer), HAM (Hybrid Annuity Model — government bears 40% traffic risk), EPC (government bears all risk, purely a contractor arrangement — technically not PPP).",
        highlight: "BOT-Toll | BOT-Annuity | DBFOT | HAM | EPC | NHAI | Concession Period | VGF | Traffic Risk"
