          "HAM suits Project Y: NHAI pays 40% mobilisation during construction → private risks only 60%. Post-completion: government pays annuity regardless of traffic. Private earns predictable return.",
          "For Project Y, if HAM still not commercially attractive → consider BOT-Annuity (100% annuity, no traffic risk for private) or even EPC (NHAI funds entirely).",
          "Bank financing: HAM project — banks lend against government annuity payments (sovereign payment obligation) → lower credit risk → favourable rates."
