        opts: ["Risk Appetite is quantitative; Risk Capacity is only qualitative", "Risk Capacity is the maximum risk the bank can absorb before failing; Risk Appetite is the risk the bank chooses to accept (always lower than capacity)", "They are the same concept used interchangeably in banking", "Risk Appetite is set by RBI; Risk Capacity is set by the bank's Board"],
