          "Capital saving = ₹1.8 − ₹0.72 = ₹1.08 crore (60% capital reduction for this AAA loan).",
          "SA over-charges capital for high-quality borrowers (AAA). IRB correctly captures the low PD.",
          "But: Basel IV Output Floor: if SA RWA = ₹20 Cr, then IRB RWA must be at least 72.5% × ₹20 Cr = ₹14.5 Cr.",
          "Post-floor capital = ₹14.5 Cr × 9% = ₹1.305 Cr — less saving than pre-floor, but still beneficial vs pure SA."
