        body: "Portfolio credit risk models assess the credit risk of the ENTIRE loan portfolio, capturing correlation effects. Two prominent models: CreditMetrics (J.P. Morgan, 1997) — uses credit rating transition matrices and asset correlations to simulate portfolio value distribution. KMV Model (Moody's Analytics) — uses structural (Merton) model where default occurs when asset value falls below debt level; estimates PD from equity market data. Both models generate a loss distribution for the portfolio from which VaR, CVaR, and Economic Capital can be derived. Key insight: loan correlation (sector, geography, systematic factor) dramatically affects portfolio tail loss — highly correlated portfolios are riskier even with same individual EL.",
