        body: "The Fundamental Review of the Trading Book (FRTB, Basel January 2019) is a comprehensive overhaul of market risk capital standards. Key changes: (1) ES at 97.5% replaces VaR at 99%, (2) clearer trading book / banking book boundary (frequent profit-taking = trading book), (3) Internal Model Approach (IMA) requires desk-level approval + P&L Attribution Test + backtesting, (4) Revised Standardised Approach (SA-FRTB) is more risk-sensitive than old SA, (5) 72.5% output floor applies (SA-FRTB minimum for IMA banks). FRTB significantly increases market risk capital for many banks — especially those with complex derivatives and securitisation exposures. India: RBI implementing FRTB from 2025.",
