        body: "Operational Risk (OpRisk) is defined by Basel as 'the risk of loss resulting from inadequate or failed internal processes, people, and systems or from external events.' It explicitly includes legal risk but excludes strategic and reputational risk. Basel II/III classifies OpRisk losses into 7 event types. OpRisk is the third pillar of Pillar 1 capital (after credit and market). Unlike credit and market risk, OpRisk has no specific underlying asset — it arises from operational failures. Key metrics: gross loss amount, net loss (after recovery/insurance), number of events, near-miss incidents.",
