        body: "Effective Operational Risk Management requires proactive identification of risks before they materialise into losses. Three complementary tools: RCSA (Risk and Control Self-Assessment) — identifies risks and evaluates control effectiveness. KRI (Key Risk Indicators) — metrics that signal changing risk levels before losses occur. LDC (Loss Data Collection) — systematic collection and analysis of operational loss events. Together, these form the foundation of a bank's ORM infrastructure. They feed into: capital calculation (AMA/SMA), management decisions, ICAAP, and board risk reporting. RBI expects banks to have all three components as part of their operational risk management framework.",
