        body: "Risk governance establishes clear accountability for risk across all levels of an organisation. Board-level governance: the Board Risk Committee (BRC) is a standing committee of the Board, comprised of independent directors, responsible for setting risk appetite, approving risk policies, and overseeing risk management effectiveness. Management-level governance: the Risk Management Committee (RMC) — chaired by MD/CEO, includes CRO, CFO, heads of business lines — implements the BRC's risk framework. The CRO (Chief Risk Officer) leads the independent risk function. RBI's Corporate Governance guidelines (2021) made BRC mandatory for all banks with assets >₹5,000 crore.",
