        title: "Recovery Planning: Preparing for the Worst",
        body: "Recovery and Resolution Planning (RRP) ensures that even large, systemically important banks can be resolved without taxpayer bailouts or systemic disruption. Recovery Plan (Living Will — Part A): bank-authored plan for how it will restore financial health if it faces severe stress — through capital raising, asset sales, business restructuring. Resolution Plan (Living Will — Part B): regulator/resolution authority plan for how the bank will be wound up if recovery fails — without systemic risk. RBI/Government under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (Financial Service Providers) and proposed FRDI Bill framework address resolution. FSB's Key Attributes of Effective Resolution (2011) is the global standard.",
        highlight: "Recovery Plan | Resolution Plan | Living Will | D-SIB | FRDI | NCLT | Bail-in | Gone Concern | MREL/TLAC"
