          "Option (d) Dividend suspension: Immediate — conserves earnings in capital. Cost: investor dissatisfaction. Implement immediately.",
          "Option (c) Loan book growth reduction: Reduces RWA growth → slows CRAR erosion. Implement immediately (new credit sanctions reduced).",
          "Option (b) Insurance subsidiary sale: Can raise capital quickly if market is receptive. Timeline: 3-6 months (regulatory approval). Initiate process while implementing (d) and (c).",
          "Option (a) Rights issue: Largest and most certain capital boost but takes 6-9 months (shareholder approval, SEBI, RBI). Plan simultaneously with (b).",
          "Sequence: D+C (immediate) → B (3-6 months) → A (6-9 months). If CRAR continues to fall below 9.5% → trigger RBI intervention protocol. Notify RBI of Recovery Plan activation."
