        body: "The 70-20-10 model (Lombardo & Eichinger) suggests learning comes from: 70% challenging experiences (on-job), 20% feedback/relationships (coaching, mentoring), 10% formal training. On-job Training (OJT): job rotation, deputisation, special projects, committee membership, coaching by supervisor, understudy. Off-job Training: classroom (case study, lecture, role play, simulation), outdoor/outbound, laboratory training (T-groups). Computer-Based Training (CBT): self-paced e-learning modules, simulations, virtual reality. LMS (Learning Management System): tracks completion, assessment scores, certification — Cornerstone OnDemand, SAP SuccessFactors. Banking-specific: NIBM (National Institute of Bank Management), IIBF (Indian Institute of Banking & Finance), Bank training colleges (SBILT, Canara Bank Staff College). JAIIB/CAIIB: professional certifications for bankers — CAIIB (this exam!) demonstrates advanced management competence. Blended learning: combination of face-to-face and digital — most effective for complex skill development.",
