        body: "Total Rewards = all financial and non-financial rewards that attract, motivate, and retain employees. Components: (1) Base Pay; (2) Variable Pay — short-term incentive (STI: annual bonus, quarterly sales bonus) + long-term incentive (LTI: ESOPs, RSUs, performance shares); (3) Benefits (PF, insurance, leave); (4) Recognition — non-monetary: awards, public acknowledgement, chairman's club; (5) Work-Life Balance; (6) Career Development. Motivation theories: Herzberg's two-factor theory — Hygiene factors (pay, benefits, working conditions) prevent dissatisfaction but don't motivate; Motivators (achievement, recognition, growth) drive engagement. Vroom's Expectancy Theory: Motivation = Expectancy × Instrumentality × Valence — employee effort only if they believe: (a) effort leads to performance, (b) performance leads to reward, (c) reward is valued. Variable pay in PSBs: Performance-Linked Pay (PLP) introduced in 12th BPS — nominal (3-10% of monthly pay for top performers). Private banks: at-risk pay 15-30% of CTC for front-line; 30-50%+ for senior managers. ESOPs: long-term retention (vesting 3-4 years) + performance alignment.",
