        body: "Grievance = employee's dissatisfaction or feeling of unjust treatment by the employer, connected with employment. Grievance handling procedure (GHP): Step 1 — Employee raises grievance verbally with immediate supervisor (5 working days to resolve); Step 2 — Written grievance to HOD if not resolved (7 days); Step 3 — HR Department (14 days); Step 4 — Grievance Committee (joint management-union body); Step 5 — IDA dispute machinery (conciliation/tribunal) if still unresolved. Benefits of effective GHP: prevents small irritants from becoming industrial disputes, identifies systemic HR issues, demonstrates management fairness. Domestic Enquiry = quasi-judicial investigation conducted by employer into alleged employee misconduct, before imposing punishment. Principles of natural justice: (1) Audi alteram partem — hear both sides (employee must be given opportunity to present defence); (2) Nemo judex in causa sua — no one should be a judge in their own cause (enquiry officer must be impartial). Domestic enquiry: charge sheet → reply by employee → enquiry officer appointed → evidence (management presents first, employee cross-examines) → findings → punishment if proved. Enquiry officer's finding ≠ final punishment — disciplinary authority decides punishment.",
