        body: "Agricultural NPAs have multiple causes: (1) Natural calamities — drought, flood, pest attack causing crop failure and income loss; (2) Price volatility — price crash at harvest (onion, potato) makes loan repayment impossible; (3) Multiple loans — farmer over-indebted (KCC + housing + PMEGP + family credit); (4) Willful default — 'moneylender mentality' of not repaying banks (perceived as government money); (5) Documentation weaknesses — land records dispute, KCC granted without visiting farm; (6) Political loan waivers — moral hazard (expectation of waiver reduces incentive to repay). NPA statistics: Priority sector/agri NPAs higher than non-PSL; RRBs have higher agri NPA %. Recovery mechanisms: (1) Lok Adalat — pre-litigation settlement; (2) DRT — for loans >₹20 lakh; (3) Revenue Recovery Act (State Acts) — land revenue officials assist in agri loan recovery (quasi-legal); (4) Restructuring under NPA norms; (5) SARFAESI (for agriculture loans with eligible collateral); (6) One Time Settlement (OTS). Challenges: social pressure not to use SARFAESI against farmers; political interference; court stays. Moral hazard of loan waivers: empirically shown to reduce credit discipline (Chaudhuri & Gupta study).",
